obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_352  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Exposure of mossy fibre neurons to Wnt7-containing culture medium derived from cerebellar granule cells increases the density of VAMP2, synapsin 1 and Bassoon puncta along axons. This is supported by an increase in the number of recycling synaptic vesicle sites as identified using antibodies against synaptotagmin-1 or FM1-43 labelling.\n\nConversely, VAMP2 puncta and number of recycling synaptic vesicle sites were significantly decreased in Dvl1 mutant mice or when Wnt7b signalling was interrupted by treatment with the Wnt inhibitor Sfrp-1. Dvl1 mutant mice further showed a decrease in the amount of synapsin 1 accumulating at cerebellar glomerular rosettes.\n\n27/3/2017 Pim\n- Since Dvl1 is a presumed scaffold of developing synapses I agree to (1) not select the \"regulates ...\" option and to (2) not advise a second annotation against \"Wnt sinaling pathway in the presynapse\" (Dvl1 does not signal).. Experimental description: Materials and Methods \"Basilar pontine nuclei from wild-type, Dvl1 mutant, or Wnt7a-/-;Dvl1-/- mutant mice were dissected from newborn or P1 pups, cut into 100-μm2 explants, and cultured in 16-well LabTeck chamber slides, as previously described\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_352" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

